article.headline: Indiana St. 65, N. Iowa 61
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- Justin Gant scored 18 points and Jake Odum 16 to lead Indiana State to a 65-61 victory against Northern Iowa on Wednesday night. The Sycamores (9-4, 2-0 Missouri Valley) never trailed after 3:43 remained in the first half and held on despite making just 4 of 8 from the free-throw line in the last 34 seconds. Trailing by three points, Northern Iowa called its final timeout with 6.5 seconds left to set up a final play. But the Panthers (7-7, 0-2) turned the ball over, and Lucas Eitel hit a free throw for Indiana State. Seth Tuttle had 24 points and 10 rebounds and James Anthony added 12 points for Northern Iowa. Gant was 8 of 12 from the field with six rebounds.
